        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 5:59PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Givens Hot Springs, or 11 miles southwest of Nampa, moving north at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lake Lowell around 600 PM MDT.
Nampa around 620 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
